### Create a figure [POST]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here.",
            "related_figures":[],
            "related_stories":[],
            "related_cultures":["/api/cultures/3/"],
        }

+ Response 201 (text/html)

        Location: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/figures/4/
        
## Figure [/figures/{id}]
+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Figure to perform action with. Has example value.
    
### Edit a figure [PUT]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "title":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here.",
            "related_figures":[],
            "related_stories":[],
            "related_cultures":["/api/cultures/3/"],
        }

+ Response 204


+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Figure to perform action with. Has example value.

### Retrieve a figure [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id":4,
            "name":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here.",
            "related_figures":[],
            "related_stories":[],
            "related_cultures":["/api/cultures/3/"],
            "resource_uri":"/api/figures/4/"
        }

### Remove a figure [DELETE]
+ Response 204

